<p>Appleâ€™s <a href="https://sixcolors.com/link/2021/11/apple-launches-a-consumer-self-service-repair-program-for-iphones/">Self Service Repair program</a>, which was announced in 2021 and updated in 2022 to cover <a href="https://sixcolors.com/post/2022/08/apple-brings-self-service-repair-to-the-mac/">Mac laptops</a> and <a href="https://sixcolors.com/link/2022/12/apples-self-repair-program-adds-mac-desktops/">Mac desktops</a>, has now added iPad repair to the mix.</p>
<p>According to Apple, beginning Thursday the company will offer support for repairs on iPad Air (M2 and later), iPad Pro (M4), iPad mini (A17 Pro), and iPad (A16), covering displays, batteries, cameras, and charging ports. The program, which already covers the U.S. and Europe, will expand to Canada this summer, Apple said.</p>
